Preheat the oven to 180C/350F/Gas 4.Place the flour, sugar, peanut butter, egg yolk and butter into a large bowl and mix together until combined to a smooth dough.With lightly floured hands, break off evenly sized pieces of the dough and roll into walnut sized balls.Place the dough balls onto a baking sheet lined with silicon paper or baking parchment and gently press each ball with the back of a fork to flatten slightly.Place in the oven and bake for ten minutes, or until just turning golden-brown.Transfer the cookies to a wire rack and allow to cool for ten minutes.To serve, place on a serving plate and dust with icing sugar.